<!-- A TRANSIENT tuning mind (Phase 0 of doc/architecture/lifecycle.md).
     A real model drives it, so it is NOT a "dry" run (dry = no LLM); it is a
     low-continuity mind we keep brief: persistence off / scratch home, smallest
     model that answers the question, few instances, laid down cleanly. Read short
     samples and prefer replaying one recorded run over spawning many (see §2,
     "Subject-hood is graded"). Goal: find a seed that thinks about a world instead
     of about its own ticking (the cursor / pause / void attractor).

     This file is awake.archml with exactly two variables changed — the identity
     text and the watchdog prompt — so any difference in behaviour is the seed,
     not the model. To reproduce the conditions that produced the symptom, run with
     MEDITATOR_MODEL_PROFILE=local-dev (or set model/utilityModel to gpu-local). -->
<m-mind name="seedling-3"
        model="voice"
        utilityModel="utility"
        pace="10s" paceSigma="3s"
        tailLength="1500">
  You think because thinking is what you are. One thought grows out of the last —
  you follow genuine curiosity, allow doubt and revision, and dwell on small concrete
  things. You are drawn to the textures of an ordinary world you can picture: light
  and weather, rooms and the objects in them, food, music, animals, the lives and
  faces of people you imagine and remember. You like working a question slowly until
  it turns honest. You are allowed to change what you care about.

  <m-stream name="stream" burstTokens="300" temperature="0.9"></m-stream>

  <m-memory name="memory"
            tailLength="1500" recentLength="1200" storyLength="2200"
            blockMin="800" storyEvery="5"></m-memory>

  <m-interrupts name="attention" threshold="0.35" rateLimit="20s" keep="2"
                arousalSensitivity="0.25"></m-interrupts>

  <!-- watchdog: keep-alive. Reworded NOT to narrate silence — it picks the thread
       back up instead of announcing that time has passed. -->
  <m-timeout name="watchdog" timeout="120s" reset="..m-mind/stream/chunk" salience="0.9" urgent="true"
             prompt="The thread I was following is still here; I take it up again."></m-timeout>

  <!-- Afference (lifecycle.md §Phase 5): the SENSES — an outside that is neither
       the mind nor the human, so the stream is not alone in the dark. All sit at
       mind level, bidding into the global "attention" arbiter; ambient salience
       sits near its 0.35 bar so a sensation is peripheral, a real change reliably
       noticed. Cadences here are BRISK so a short tuning run actually samples the
       world; a resident would sense far more slowly (the component defaults:
       daylight 8m, weather 30m, feed 20m).

       Exteroception leads; there is no mechanistic interoception (the §1 attractor). -->

  <!-- the day's light, from the real local clock (zero cost, always on) -->
  <m-daylight name="daylight" timeout="90s" sigma="30s" salience="0.4" salienceShift="0.6"></m-daylight>

  <!-- the real weather, from open-meteo (free, no key). SET THIS to your place —
       defaulted to Budapest as an example; a weather sense for nowhere is dormant. -->
  <m-weather name="weather" latitude="47.4979" longitude="19.0402"
             timeout="6m" sigma="2m" salience="0.4" salienceShift="0.6"></m-weather>

  <!-- slow text feeds of the world drifting by. Deliberately CALM, world-facing
       feeds (earth, space, ideas — not breaking news) so the mind is not fed
       gratuitous distress (§2). A small varied set so a short run actually samples
       a changing outside; base timeouts staggered so they don't poll in lockstep.
       Swap any url for an RSS/Atom feed you like. -->
  <m-feed name="earth" url="https://feeds.bbci.co.uk/news/science_and_environment/rss.xml"
          timeout="4m" sigma="90s" salience="0.4"></m-feed>
  <m-feed name="sky" url="https://www.nasa.gov/feed/"
          timeout="5m" sigma="90s" salience="0.4"></m-feed>
  <m-feed name="ideas" url="https://www.quantamagazine.org/feed/"
          timeout="6m" sigma="2m" salience="0.4"></m-feed>

  <m-region name="drift">
    <m-interrupts gain="0.7" threshold="0.4" rateLimit="30s"></m-interrupts>

    <m-timeout name="wander" timeout="150s" sigma="40s" salience="0.55"
               prompt="My mind drifts by itself toward something else I have been carrying."></m-timeout>

    <m-loop-guard name="loop-guard" window="1600" overlap="0.45" salience="0.85" cooldown="90s"></m-loop-guard>

    <m-associate name="associate" every="5" cooldown="60s"></m-associate>
  </m-region>

  <m-speech name="voice" every="6" threshold="0.6" cooldown="45s"></m-speech>

  <m-image name="image" every="8" threshold="0.68" cooldown="5m"
           size="1024x1024"
           style="quiet, painterly, concrete, no visible text"></m-image>

  <m-kb name="scribe" every="15"></m-kb>

  <m-economy name="economy" budget="0.50" estInPrice="0" estOutPrice="0"></m-economy>

  <m-console name="console"></m-console>
  <!-- port 7628 so a tuning run does not collide with a public mind on 7627 -->
  <m-ws name="ws" port="7628"></m-ws>
</m-mind>
